responses.text:
Their flags and their banners they are waving with joy and excitement they shout—
A tide of new voices, a tapestry bright, spilling hope as it ripples throughout.
The faces are glowing, the hands are held high, a vision of futures remade;
Each step writes a promise, each chant is a bond, in sunlight that cannot be swayed.
O’er city and country, the banners unfurl, inscribed with the dreams of the crowd;
And joy, like a banner, flies high on the wind, in a chorus triumphant and loud.

Go, go, my naughty girl, and kiss
the morning with your rebel grin;
let daring dreams and wishes twist
like ribbons, tangled on your skin.
Steal honeyed laughter from the breeze,
dance barefoot through the meadow’s song;
for every rule you play to tease,
the world grows brighter, bold, and strong.
So chase the day, my wild delight,
with kisses sown in gleeful flight.

Go, go, my naughty girl, and kiss
the cheek of dusk before it fades;
let twilight blush beneath your touch,
your laughter ringing through the glades.
With every impish, gleaming glance,
you turn the shadows into light;
through gentle trouble, take your chance,
and leave the world a bit more bright.
May kisses flutter as you roam,
a wild heart, forever home.

Go, go, my naughty girl, and kiss
the thunder in the summer storm;
let boldness be your only bliss,
your spirit free, your mischief warm.
Chase raindrops on an open lane,
whisper secrets to the breeze;
your laughter breaking every chain,
your kisses carried where you please.
So onward, wild and full of cheer,
embrace the world without a fear.

Farewell, thou child of my right hand, and joy;  
A silver thread unwinding in the dawn,  
A laugh that gleamed like sunlight on a toy—  
How quietly the golden days are gone.  
Your footprints linger still upon the floor,  
Your whispered dreams unravel in my mind;  
To memory’s gentle gate I turn once more,  
And there, your spirit waiting, soft I find.  
Farewell, sweet kin, bright echo in my song;  
Though shadows fall, my love endures so long.
